Package: veriforge
Version: 1.0.0
Section: devel
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: Muhammad Bilal <bilalsajid695@gmail.com>
Depends: python3 (>= 3.10), python3-pip, python3-venv
Recommends: iverilog, gtkwave
Suggests: verilator
Description: Verilog RTL simulation IDE with waveform viewer
 VeriForge is a desktop IDE for writing, simulating, and debugging
 Verilog and SystemVerilog designs. It runs Icarus Verilog in the
 background, parses VCD output, and displays interactive waveforms
 in a built-in viewer — no GTKWave required.
 .
 Features:
  - Tabbed editor with Verilog/SV syntax highlighting
  - One-click simulation via iverilog + vvp
  - Interactive VCD waveform viewer (zoom, pan, markers, export)
  - YAML-driven module and testbench code generation
  - TCL scripting console (Vivado-style)
  - Six themes including Dracula default
  - Full RV32I example included
Homepage: https://github.com/engrbilal992/veriforge
